    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - POWER STEERING GEAR: SHEPPARD MODEL 292, 392, 492 - DISASSEMBLE - SHORT SERIES
        HOUSING ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>SHORT SERIES HOUSING ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The bronze bearings are pre-sized and boring or honing is not required (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0500449">Figure 49</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f0500449" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0500449" filename="../figg05/g0500449.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 49. Bronze Bearings</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the quad ring oil seal from the gear housing and discard (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500450">Figure 50</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500450" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500450" filename="../figg05/g0500450.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 50. Remove Quad Ring Oil Seal and Discard</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a drift punch to drive the bronze bearing out of the housing. Alternately tap one side
                of the bearing and then at an opposite side to keep it moving evenly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500451">Figure 51</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500451" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500451" filename="../figg05/g0500451.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 51. Drive Bronze Bearing Out of Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Withdraw the bronze bearing from the cover with a suitable bushing remover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500452">Figure 52</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500452" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500452" filename="../figg05/g0500452.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 52. Withdraw Bronze Bearing From Cover</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
